"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783204","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-13","<p>It is longstanding practice under successive Governments that we do not routinely disclose information relating to internal discussion and advice. My right hon. Friend the member for Witham (Ms Patel) resigned as Secretary of State for International Development on 8 November. I refer the Hon Member to the exchange of letters between my right hon. Friend and the Prime Minister on her resignation; and to the statement issued by my right hon. Friend on 6 November, a copy of which is available on the <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">gov.uk</a> website.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-11-13T17:45:29.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783204/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783204/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-03","Department for International Development: Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he was made aware of meetings in Israel held by the Secretary of State for International Development in August 2017; and what information he has since been given about what was discussed at those meetings.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","111361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783205","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-13","<p>​In FY16-17 ​the Department spent 10 per cent through Government Crown Commercial Service (CCS) Strategic Suppliers.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-11-13T17:52:53.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783205/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783205/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-03","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what proportion of his Department's spend in the last year has been with Government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","111284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783206","Department for International Trade","false","2017-11-13","<p>We are considering our future trading relationships with a broad range of partners as we prepare to leave the EU. The UK remains committed to ensuring developing countries can reduce poverty through enhanced trading opportunities. The Government’s priority is to deliver continuity in our trading arrangements, including with developing countries. We will seek to transition existing Economic Partnership Agreements with African, and also Pacific and Caribbean, countries and regions. We will establish a unilateral trade preference scheme which will, as a minimum, provide the same level of access to around 70 developing countries as the EU’s Generalised Scheme of Preferences.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-11-13T17:15:31.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783206/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783206/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-11-03","Trade Agreements: Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that trade negotiations include low and middle-income countries in Africa when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","111319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783207","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-13","<p>The Government continues to support The Gambia's transition to democracy. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office is funding a special advisor in the Minister of Justice's office to drive forward constitutional, institutional and legal reforms, as well as providing human rights training to the State Intelligence Service as part of the wider agenda on security sector reform. We are considering how we can build on the recent activities undertaken by the Commonwealth Parliamentary Association UK and Westminster Foundation for Democracy in strengthening good governance and transparency in Parliament.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-11-13T14:35:27.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783207/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783207/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-03","Gambia: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to support the Gambia's transition to democracy.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","111322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783208","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-13","<p>​The UK Government is extremely concerned about the case of Raif Badawi. The UK Government understands the case is still under consideration in the Saudi Supreme Court, but we do not expect further lashes to be administered. Saudi Arabia remains a Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office (FCO) human rights priority country and we raise our concerns with the Saudi Arabian authorities using a range of Ministerial and diplomatic channels of communication, including our Ambassador, the Embassy and the European Union delegation in Riyadh. FCO officials in Riyadh meet regularly with their EU and US counterparts to discuss this case and other cases of concern.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-11-13T17:39:36.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783208/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783208/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-03","Raif Badawi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have met their counterparts in the (i) EU and (ii) US to discuss the case of Raif Badawi in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","111410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783209","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-13","<p>The British Government believes that the Commonwealth is a force for good around the world, through its promotion of democracy, the rule of law, good governance and economic development, as enshrined in the Commonwealth Charter. The 2018 Commonwealth Heads of Government meeting in London will encourage all members to uphold these values</p><p>As the Prime Minister set out in September, the key goals of the summit will include promoting democracy and boosting prosperity across the Commonwealth, including in low and middle-income countries. We want to see The Gambia fully included as part of that wider effort.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-11-13T14:41:40.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783209/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783209/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783209/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-03","Commonwealth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what plans his Department has to ensure that Commonwealth nations help to tackle economic problems and to embed democracy in (a) the Gambia and (b) other low and middle-income countries; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","111436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783210","Department of Health","false","2017-11-13","<p>£21 million of capital funding will be allocated to major trauma centres and ambulance trusts by the end of December 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The funding supports those organisations to make required information technology investments that:</p><p> </p><p>- Secure their network by upgrading firewalls;</p><p>- Improve network resilience and segmentation to minimise risk to medical devices;</p><p>- Improve device security by replacing obsolete PCs and the introduction of tools to support the automation of patch management; and</p><p>- Improve anti-virus protection.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-11-13T17:41:37.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783210/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783210/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783210/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-03","NHS: Computer Software","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 3 November 2017 to Question 110492, on NHS: computer software, what that £21 million will be spent on and over what period of time.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","111395"
