"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783223","Home Office","false","2017-11-14","<p>The Home Office does not hold information on the proportion of regulated animal procedures which are funded, or part-funded, by registered charities.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"2017-11-14T15:08:03.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783223/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783223/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-03","Animal Experiments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of regulated animal procedures conducted in 2016 were funded, or part-funded, by registered charities.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","111373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783224","Home Office","false","2017-11-14","<p>The Home Office ensures that animal research and testing is carried out only where no practicable alternative exists, and under controls which keep suffering to the minimum. This is achieved through robustly applying the principles of the 3Rs which require that, in every research proposal, animals are replaced with non-animal alternatives wherever possible; that the number of animals used is reduced to the minimum needed to achieve the results sought; and that, for those animals which must be used, procedures are refined as much as possible to minimise their suffering.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"2017-11-14T14:47:44.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783224/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783224/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-03","Animal Experiments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to reduce use of live animals in experiments.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","111374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783225","Home Office","false","2017-11-13","<p>During FY1617, Home Office spent 27.7% of its total third party spend with Government strategic suppliers.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2017-11-13T17:55:19.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783225/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783225/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-03","Home Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of her Department's spend in the last year has been with Government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","111286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783226","Home Office","false","2017-11-13","<p>The existing legislation contains a number of protections to ensure legal records for births are maintained accurately and, in the case of deceased unmarried fathers, these include a requirement to obtain a court declaration of parentage. There are no current plans to amend the legislation.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-11-13T17:46:08.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783226/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783226/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783226/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-03","Registration of Births, Deaths, Marriages and Civil Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will amend legislation on births, deaths and marriages to remove the requirement to register DNA of a deceased father on a birth certificate where paternity is not contested.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","111270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783227","Home Office","false","2017-11-27","<p>We are aware of a formal complaint being made against the Independent Anti-Slavery Commissioner towards another organisation and we are taking the appropriate action.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2017-11-27T17:59:33.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783227/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783227/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-03","Independent Anti-slavery Commissioner","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she has received any formal complaints on the conduct of the Independent Anti-Slavery Commissioner.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","111296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783228","Home Office","false","2017-11-13","<p>The Government strongly supports the principle of family unity, and we have a comprehensive framework in place for refugees and their families to be safely reunited in the UK without the need for dangerous journeys.</p><p>Our family reunion policy allows children to join their refugee parents, and there are also specific provisions in the Immigration Rules that allow extended family members lawfully resident in the UK to sponsor unaccompanied children where there are serious and compelling circumstances.</p><p>We have reunited over 24,000 partners and children with their families under our family reunion policy in the last five years. Further, those children recognised by UNHCR as refugees can join close family members in the UK through our Mandate resettlement scheme.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-11-13T17:47:11.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783228/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783228/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-03","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to reduce dangerous journeys for unaccompanied child refugees with family in the UK.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","111408"
