"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783231","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-13","<p>My Rt Hon Friend the member for Witham (Ms Patel) resigned as Secretary of State for International Development on 8 November. I refer the Hon Gentleman to the exchange of letters between my Rt Hon Friend and my Rt Hon Friend the Prime Minister on her resignation; and to the statement issued by my Rt Hon Friend on 6 November:<br>https://www.gov.uk/government/news/statement-from-international-development-secretary-priti-patel</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-11-13T16:47:54.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783231/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783231/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-03","Department for International Development: Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will list the meetings she held in Israel during August 2017; who was present at those meetings; and what was discussed at each of those meetings.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","111363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783232","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-13","<p>My Rt Hon Friend the member for Witham (Ms Patel) resigned as Secretary of State for International Development on 8 November. I refer the Hon Lady to the exchange of letters between my Rt Hon Friend and my Rt Hon Friend the Prime Minister on her resignation; and to the statement issued by my Rt Hon Friend on 6 November:<br>https://www.gov.uk/government/news/statement-from-international-development-secretary-priti-patel</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-11-13T16:48:40.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783232/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783232/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783232/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-03","Department for International Development: Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what meetings she has had in Israel with which officials since June 2017.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","111343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783233","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-13","<p>The Department holds no information about meetings between my Rt Hon Friend the member for Witham in the West Bank with Palestinian Authority officials since June 2017.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-11-13T16:49:57.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783233/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783233/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783233/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-03","Department for International Development: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what meetings she has had in the West Bank with Palestinian Authority officials since June 2017.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","111344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783234","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-13","<p>The personal injury discount rate set by the Lord Chancellor for England and Wales under section 1 of the Damages Act 1996 was reduced from 2.5% to minus 0.75% on 20 March following a review. The Lord Chancellor is required by law to make sure the rate is not inappropriate.</p><p> </p><p>On 7 September, the Ministry of Justice published and invited comments on draft legislation that would, if enacted, change the way in which the discount rate is set and require a review of the rate to be started within 90 days of the legislation coming into force and completed within 180 days of the start of the review. The Justice Select Committee is conducting a pre-legislative scrutiny inquiry into the draft legislation.</p><p> </p><p>Subject to the response to the draft legislation, the Government intends to legislate promptly to make sure that the way the rate is set is put on the best possible footing at the earliest practicable date. The first review of the rate will then be carried out in accordance with the terms of the legislation.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-11-13T16:48:26.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783234/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783234/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783234/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-03","Personal Injury: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when his Department plans to review the personal injury discount rate.","true","Biography information for Craig Tracey","North Warwickshire","Craig Tracey","111371"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783235","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-13","<p>The proportion of spend by the Ministry of Justice for the financial year 2016/2017 with the Government’s strategic suppliers was £1,436,976,342; 31% of the total spend of the Ministry of Justice for this period.</p><p> </p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-11-13T16:10:56.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783235/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783235/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-03","Ministry of Justice: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of his Department's spend in the last year has been with Government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","111289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783236","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-13","<p>Prisons are free to decide locally how they participate in Holocaust Memorial Day, Black History Month and National Hate Crime Awareness Week. Such participation will reflect the needs of individual prisons in terms of their offender and staffing profiles. National Prison Radio promotes national support for local initiatives, and Her Majesty’s Prison and Probation Service also provides information to prisons via its staff networks to support prison staff in their participation in local events.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-11-13T16:10:45.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783236/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783236/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-03","Prisons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department has taken to support prisons to participate in (a) Holocaust Memorial Day, (b) Black History Month and (c) National Hate Crime Awareness Week.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","111268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783237","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-13","<p>The number of offenders sentenced to a community order, in England and Wales, from 2010 to 2016 (latest available), with those sentenced for violence against the person and sexual offences separately identifiable and selectable for 2016 alone, can be found in the Criminal Justice Statistics data tool as part of the Criminal Justice Statistics quarterly (December 2016), linked below, on gov.uk.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2016</a></p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","111317","2017-11-13T16:49:00.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783237/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783237/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-03","Community Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many community orders for non-violent offences have been made in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","111316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783238","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-13","<p>The number of offenders sentenced to a community order, in England and Wales, from 2010 to 2016 (latest available), with those sentenced for violence against the person and sexual offences separately identifiable and selectable for 2016 alone, can be found in the Criminal Justice Statistics data tool as part of the Criminal Justice Statistics quarterly (December 2016), linked below, on gov.uk.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2016</a></p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","111316","2017-11-13T16:49:01.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783238/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/783238/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-03","Community Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many community orders for violent and sexual offences were made last year.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","111317"
